# Caboodle CSS Rules

## Architecture

CSS is split into three files imported by `main.css` in this order:

1. **`tokens.css`** — Design tokens only (custom properties on `:root`)
2. **`layouts.css`** — Every Layout primitives (DO NOT modify for page-specific needs)
3. **`components.css`** — All site-specific component styles

## Adding new styles

- **New spacing/color/typography values** → add to `tokens.css` as custom properties
- **New component styles** → add to `components.css`, grouped with related components
- **New layout needs** → compose existing primitives from `layouts.css`; do not create one-off layout classes

## Design tokens

### Spacing (modular scale, ratio 1.5)

Use `--s-5` through `--s5`. Never use raw pixel values for spacing.

```css
/* Good */
padding: var(--s1);
gap: var(--s0);
margin-block-start: var(--s2);

/* Bad */
padding: 24px;
gap: 1rem; /* use --s0 instead */
margin-top: 37px;
```

### Colors

Use token variables, not raw hex values:

- `--color-dark` (#1a1a2e) — primary text
- `--color-mid` (#4a4a68) — secondary text
- `--color-light` (#f0f0f5) — light backgrounds
- `--color-lightest` (#fafafa) — page background
- `--color-brand` (#cf3a4e) — brand red
- `--color-accent` (#2B87FF) — links, focus, interactive elements
- `--color-border` (#ccc) — borders

### Typography

- `--font-display` — headings (Georgia)
- `--font-plain` — body text (Roboto)
- `--font-mono` — code blocks

## Naming

- Use lowercase kebab-case for class names (`.obj-card`, `.guide-header`)
- Keep names semantic and descriptive of what the element represents, not how it looks
- Prefix object-related components with `obj-` (`.obj-card`, `.obj-card-stats`)
- Prefix guide-related components with `guide-` (`.guide-header`, `.guide-variations`)

## Properties

- Use logical properties: `margin-block-start` not `margin-top`, `inline-size` not `width`, `padding-inline` not `padding-left`
- Exception: `width` and `height` are acceptable for explicit element sizing (icons, avatars)
- Never use `!important` on layout-related rules
- Use `var()` references to tokens for all spacing, colors, and typography values

## Selectors

- Prefer class selectors over element selectors
- Avoid deep nesting (max 3 levels)
- Do not use ID selectors for styling
- Do not override layout primitive internals (`.stack > *`, `.grid`, etc.) from component CSS

## Component organization in `components.css`

Group related styles with a comment header:

```css
/* ----- Component Name ----- */
.component { … }
.component-child { … }
```

Existing groups include: global resets, main nav, hero, page shell, sections, cards, object cards, secondary tabs, content area, guide header, data tables, code blocks, showcases, pills/badges.
